title: Irish outlast USC
text:
By Dean Pantazi - 21 Alive University of Notre Dame Fighting Irish October 18, 2015 Updated Oct 18, 2015 at 12:04 AM EDT 
NOTRE DAME, Ind. (21 Alive) - Corey Robinson snared a ten yard touchdon pass from DeShone Kizer midway through the fourth quarter to snap a 31-31 tie and help No. 14 Notre Dame decision USC 41-31 Saturday night. 
Kizer threw for 227 yards and two touchdowns while C.J. Procise ran for 143 yards and two more tallies. 
Will Fuller caught Kizer's other touchdown pass and totaled 131 receiving yards. 
Cody Kessler passed for 365 yards and two touchdowns for USC.
